"Two plus fingers worth of crisp airy light khaki colored frothy goodness comprised of big chunky bubbles...  Excellent retention...  The top of the froth turns a much more rocky as it settles a bit...  The color is a medium bronze with a slight green apple hue when back lit...  A moderate bit of small bubbled slightly quick paced carbonation rises throughout...  A good bit of lacing clings to the sides of the glass...  Overall a really nice looking brew...  A rich warm bready biscuit aroma...  Some light caramel notes as well...  A faint whiff of hops, but not much more...  The palate is much more of the same...  A big assertive malty base tempered by only a slight bit of hops...  I'm a big fan...  The mouthfeel is on the fuller side of medium bodied...  Big and chewy...  Fills and coats the mouth evenly...  Each sip is enjoyable...  Overall this one is a rock solid APA...  I'm not 1/2 way through the Beer Camp Across America collection and this one is the leader in the club house at this point...  A very nice job by Sierra Nevada and Three Floyds...  I could see myself drinking this one with regularity if it were available by itself year round..."
