"12 ounce bottle into signature pint glass, bottled on 5/15/2014. Pours slightly cloudy bright orange amber color with a 2 finger dense off white head with great retention, that reduces to a nice cap that lingers. Nice spotty soapy lacing clings down the glass, with a moderate amount of streaming carbonation. Aromas of tangerine, grapefruit, pineapple, lemon zest, orange peel, floral, grass, caramel, bread, and floral/grassy earthiness. Nice and pleasant aromas with good balance and complexity of juicy citrus/tropical hops and moderate caramel/bready malt sweetness; with solid strength. Taste of tangerine, grapefruit, pineapple, lemon zest, orange peel, floral, grass, pine, caramel, light toast, and floral/grassy earthiness. Fair amount of pine/grassy bitterness on the finish; with lingering notes of tangerine, grapefruit, pineapple, lemon zest, orange peel, floral, grass, pine, caramel, light toast, and floral/grassy earthiness on the finish for a good bit. Nice complexity and robustness of citrus/grassy hops and moderate caramel/bready malt sweetness; with a nice crisp malt/bitterness balance and zero cloying flavors after the finish. Medium carbonation and body; with a very smooth, crisp, and fairly sticky mouthfeel that is nice. Alcohol is well hidden with minimal warming present after the finish. Overall this is a nice and pleasant pale ale. Good balance and complexity of citrus/grassy hops and moderate caramel/bready malt sweetness; and very smooth and crisp to drink. A nicely enjoyable offering."
